HEADWORD: Guide rope
<hw>Guide rope</hw>. <fld>(A⟦eum⟧ronautics)</fld> <def>A rope hung from
a balloon or dirigible so as trail along the ground for about half its
length, used to preserve altitude automatically, by variation of the
length dragging on the ground, without loss of ballast or gas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

